result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Travis R Bolssen was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Defendant Travis R Bolssen in court with attorney Mark D. Skvara.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 1:22 PM. State - has resolution. Has provided the court with cert driving record     Count 1 - plea as alleged, 3 yrs probation, 1 year conditional jail time, must be served in jail, no house arrest or electronic monitoring, fine of $3,341, suspension of driver's license for 36 months, IID for 36 months, blood draw reimbursement to WI state patrol. conditions AODA, absolute sobriety, no possession or consumption of alcohol, no entry into any bars or taverns, 200 hours community service, must attend one AA meeting per week. Count 2 - would be dismissed. Skvara - agrees. Bolssen agrees. Court - it is ultimate decision of the sheriff departments regarding electronic monitoring and jail term being served in another county. Bolseen pleads NC. Court dismisses count #2. Bolssen admits to 5 prior OWI's. Court goes over plea questionaire and finds the defendant has freely, voluntairly and inteligently enter his plea and waived his constiutional rights. Court accepts plea and adjudges guilty. State - makes final statement and asks court to follow joint recommendation. Skvara - makes final statement, 2 days credit and also asks court to follow joint recommendation. Bolssen makes final statement. Court has considered all statements from all parties (including letter of recommendation provided to the court) and will proceed to sentencing: Count 1 - Imposed and stayed sentence - 6 years, 3 years initial confinement with 3 years supervision. Stayed and place on probation for 3 years with conditons of: 1 year conditional jail time with huber and community service, court does not object to jail term served in another county or electronic monitoring, fine of $3,341 to be paid within first year of probation, suspension of driver's license for 3 years, IID in any vehicle titled or registered for 3 years, blood draw cost of reimbursement of $35 to WI state patrol, AODA and follow through with any recommendations, absolute sobriety, no possession or consumption of alcohol, no entry into any bars or taverns, 200 hours community service to be served within the first year of probation, must attend one AA/NA or similar meeting per week. 2 days credit given if revoked. Notice of providing DNA wtih surcharge. Voting and firearm rights given. Right to appeal.

Called at 1:16 PM. Travis Bolssen appears in person and without counsel. State appears by Charles Simono. Bolssen informs the court that he is still trying to get an attorney, still trying to save up enough money for an attorney. Court goes thru collaquey regarding the defendant not having an attorney today. Bolssen responds - explains why he does not have enough money for an attorney yet. Court - pay $1200.00 to Clerk of Courts office within 1 week (10/21/14) to put towards attorney fees when one is hired. Court reviews defendant's paycheck stubs. State asks for release of some of the bond posted for an attorney. Court will release $1000 of the cash bond toward an attorney after the attorney writes the COC a letter requesting it and that an attorney has been retained. Court wants the defendant to pay $100.00/month towards attorney fees commencing 11/1/14. Court - set for administrative review on 11/11/14 at 1:00 PM - defendant does not need to be here on that day and will then set the matter for AIA on 2/10/15 and PH at 1:00 PM. Bond continued at this point.
